(1694, 1, '2012-08-23 14:26:41', '2012-08-23 11:26:41', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Last January 7, 2012, fourteen of ARCC’s top managers, which include Norman K. Macapagal (Senior Vice President and General Manager) and Mercado T. Magno (Vice President and General Manager for Operations), had the opportunity to attend the workshop on “LEAN CONSTRUCTION” War on Waste held at the EEI Corporation Head Office.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As soon as they returned to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, the ARCC Management showed their determination to further improve organizational efficiency by creating the G.R.O.W. (Getting Rid Of Waste) Program.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">“We cannot rest on our laurels,” Magno said during the initial leg of the echo-seminar on Lean Construction, which he conducted last March 16, 2012 at Juaymah Central Training Room. He told the twenty-one (21) Managers who attended the seminar/workshop that while ARCC has been maximizing the utilization of its resources and is greatly benefitting from it, it should not cease from finding better ways to improve its operations.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The G.R.O.W. Program focuses on eight waste areas which should be monitored and addressed in order to achieve the principles of “Lean Construction”. These eight waste areas are: correction, department inefficiency, material movement, motion, equipment breakdown, waiting, inventory, and over processing.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">During the seminar-workshop the participants showed keen interest in implementing various programs and activities as evidenced by their respective outputs during the workshop.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The second and final batch of twenty-three (23) ARCC managers likewise underwent the echo-seminar on March 30, 2012 with ARCC’s Senior Vice President and General Manager, Mr. Norman K. Macapagal as resource speaker.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The said program shall be cascaded to the level of the Senior Staff. This will provide them vital information to successfully implement “Lean Construction” in their respective areas.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">ARCC blazes the trail towards organizational efficiency via the “G.R.O.W. Program” and shall soon get “leaner” than ever.</p>', 'ARCC: Leaner Than Ever', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1478-revision-7', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:26:41', '2012-08-23 11:26:41', '', 1478, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1694', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1453, 1, '2012-08-18 16:42:37', '2012-08-18 13:42:37', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Launching of the ARCC Fund Raising Drive for the SENDONG calamity victims held last December 22,2011, during the ARCC Year-end Celebration at Jubail Camp.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As the show started, teary-eyed employees gave their donations cheerfully with a smile knowing that with their “one Riyal” they have whole-heartedly contributed will go a long way in helping the victims of SENDONG and collected seven water bottles bursting to its lid filled with donations.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Water Bottles were used to dramatically symbolize the irony that, the water (flood waters) which ravaged the Southern Philippines would be the same water (of donation) will help resuscitate the victims of the calamity.</p>', '"Isang Riyal na Tulong sa mga Sinalanta ng Baha"', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1317-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-18 16:42:37', '2012-08-18 13:42:37', '', 1317, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/arcc/?p=1453', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
