(1705, 1, '2012-08-23 14:34:03', '2012-08-23 11:34:03', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Al Rushaid Construction Co., Ltd. has achieved another milestone in its first ASME and National Board of Inspection Code  NBIC) stamping requirements on Saudi Polymers Company / National Chevron Philips Cracking Furnaces Boiler Feed Water Modification Works Project at Al Jubail Industrial City, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The scope of work originally involves the modification of the Boiler Feed Water Coils and Headers of the Cracking Furnaces No. 41F01, 41F02 and 41F06. This means cutting the return bends on each end of the Boiler Feed Water Coils and altering the flow from an up-to-down direction to a side-toside direction. The modification of the Boiler Feed Water Coils and inlet/outlet Headers of the Cracking Furnaces is to be carried out in conjunction with ASME Section 1 Edition 2010 and NBIC (ANSI/NB23) Edition 2011. Likewise, an “R” Code direct stamp is to be placed adjacent to the original Boiler Manufacturer stamp and the Data Report will be signed by an ASME Authorized Inspector (AI) for each furnace upon completion of the modification work and the hydrostatic test.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The overall performance, competency, high productivity, and organizational efficiency put into the work by ARCC Fabrication Project Management Team, headed by Jay-Ar T. Daquel, on this project impressed the Client. The Client has awarded ARCC to perform the work of the same scope to three (3) additional cracking furnaces (Nos. 41F03, 41F05 and 41F08). The work started last October 29, 2011 and was completed on January 11, 2012, which is fifty-two (52) days ahead of contract schedule.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">“The work was tough due to the restricted and congested location, but our welders excelled, which completed the project ahead of schedule with excellent work quality and safety. Moreover, I would like to thank Hassan Al Hourani, ASME Authorized Inspector (AI) from TÜV NORD, and Nelson A. Molina, ARCC Fabrication QA/QC In-Charge, for their cooperation and exemplary inspection,” remarked Jay-Ar T. Dacquel (ARCC Fabrication In-Charge).</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">“The project attained an overall 97.51% Weld Acceptance Rate. The client was very happy and satisfied with the performance of the ARCC welders,” said Fortunato R. Solis Jr. (ARCC Sr. AVP/Corporate QA/QC).</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">“Currently, ARCC is looking for and expecting more incoming projects having ASME and NBIC stamping requirements in which ARCC is very much\r\nready and confident to mark again with another excellent performance and quality workmanship,” concluded Mercado T. Magno (ARCC VP and General Manager-Operations). Norman K. Macapagal, ARCC General Manager, expressed his deepest gratitude and warm congratulations to the Project Management Team for the job well done.</p>', 'Passes ASME and NBIC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1461-revision-10', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:34:03', '2012-08-23 11:34:03', '', 1461, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1705', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1458, 1, '2012-08-09 15:35:59', '2012-08-09 12:35:59', '<p>Taking pride in its Qurayyah Team Unity, the ARCC Team, continued to perform well in its shutdown works (boiler modification, oil burner replacement, and superheater extension work) as the project achieved another major milestone - initial firing of Boiler Unit No. 3 - on 29 January 2011 which is nine days ahead of schedule.</p>\r\n', 'Qurayyah Team Unity', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '273-revision-25', '', '', '2012-08-09 15:35:59', '2012-08-09 12:35:59', '', 273, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/arcc/?p=1458', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1459, 1, '2012-08-09 15:36:08', '2012-08-09 12:36:08', '<p>ARCC &ndash; Pipe Spool Fabrication Plant (PSFP) obtained the ASME Certificate of Authorization for the three (3) Stamps (i.e. Boiler Assembly &lsquo;A&rsquo; Pressure Piping &lsquo;PP&rsquo;, Power Boiler &lsquo;S&rsquo;) and NB Stamp (Repair / Alteration &lsquo;R&rsquo;) to construct and verify components according to ASME Code Section I, B31.1 and NB-28. US-based ASME Auditor Team together with the Authorized Inspection Agency (Supervisor and Authorized Inspector) performed the audit of the company and ascertained the company&rsquo;s compliance to the requirements stipulated in ASME Code Section I, B31.1 and NB-28. the final audit was conducted in ARCC-PSFP located in Jubail.</p>', 'Boiler Welding', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-28', '', '', '2012-08-09 15:36:08', '2012-08-09 12:36:08', '', 80, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/arcc/?p=1459', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
