(1469, 1, '2012-03-10 18:30:13', '2012-03-10 15:30:13', 'Last March 10, 2012, ARCC was given a Plaque by the PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS Carbone for being the “<strong>Most Compliant Contractor of PSA 2000 in 2011</strong>” in the Green Anode Plant and Liquid Pitch Terminal Project in Ras Az Zawr, in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia being done for the Saudi Arabian Mining Co. (Ma’aden). The plaque was given in appreciation of ARCC’s contribution to PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS’ achievement of being the “Best Contractor of the Year 2011” by Bechtel.\r\nARCC Vice President and General Manager Mercado T. Magno received the award from Michael Koch, PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS Site General Manager, in behalf of ARCC. During the awarding ceremony, ARCC was also commended for achieving <strong>3 Million Safe Manhours without Lost Time Incident</strong>.\r\nARCC’s contract with PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS involves civil, structural, mechanical, and piping works for one of the facilities within the Ma’aden Aluminium Smelter Plant. This aluminum smelter plant is believed to be the biggest in the world.\r\nARCC’s consistency in its safety practice is seen from the fact that it was awarded “<strong>Safest Contractor</strong>” by PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS in May, July, and August last year. “We would like to thank Bechtel and PSA 2000/FIVES SOLIOS for this award as well as those who are involved in this project especially our workers and staff. We could not have accomplished this feat without their cooperation and support” said Magno.', '3 Million Safe Manhours and Most HSE Compliant Contractor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '3-million-safe-manhours-and-most-hse-compliant-contractor', '', '', '2012-08-27 10:15:47', '2012-08-27 07:15:47', '', 0, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/arcc/?p=1469', 0, 'post', '', 0),
