(1523, 1, '2012-08-11 17:18:55', '2012-08-11 14:18:55', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">On March 12, 2012, the Solios Project celebrated another milestone for achieving 3,000,000 Safe Manhours without Lost Time Incident in the construction of the biggest Aluminum Smelter Plant in the world. The plant is a joint venture project of Maaden and ALCOA. </p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">ARCC is the contractor for the Civil and SMPP Erection Works.</p>', 'Aluminum Smelter Plant Project', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1474-revision-2', '', '', '2012-08-11 17:18:55', '2012-08-11 14:18:55', '', 1474, 'http://localhost/arcc/arcc/?p=1523', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1524, 1, '2012-08-11 17:29:27', '2012-08-11 14:29:27', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Last January 7, 2012, fourteen of ARCC’s top managers, which include Norman K. Macapagal (Senior Vice President and General Manager) and Mercado T. Magno (Vice President and General Manager for Operations), had the opportunity to attend the workshop on “LEAN CONSTRUCTION” War on Waste held at the EEI Corporation Head Office.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As soon as they returned to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, the ARCC Management showed their determination to further improve organizational efficiency by creating the G.R.O.W. (Getting Rid Of Waste) Program.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">“We cannot rest on our laurels,” Magno said during the initial leg of the echo-seminar on Lean Construction, which he conducted last March 16, 2012 at Juaymah Central Training Room. He told the twenty-one (21) Managers who attended the seminar/workshop that while ARCC has been maximizing the utilization of its resources and is greatly benefitting from it, it should not cease from finding better ways to improve its operations.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The G.R.O.W. Program focuses on eight waste areas which should be monitored and addressed in order to achieve the principles of “Lean Construction”. These eight waste areas are: correction, department inefficiency, material movement, motion, equipment breakdown, waiting, inventory, and over processing.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">During the seminar-workshop the participants showed keen interest in implementing various programs and activities as evidenced by their respective outputs during the workshop.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The second and final batch of twenty-three (23) ARCC managers likewise underwent the echo-seminar on March 30, 2012 with ARCC’s Senior Vice President and General Manager, Mr. Norman K. Macapagal as resource speaker.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The said program shall be cascaded to the level of the Senior Staff. This will provide them vital information to successfully implement “Lean Construction” in their respective areas.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">ARCC blazes the trail towards organizational efficiency via the “G.R.O.W. Program” and shall soon get “leaner” than ever.</p>', 'ARCC: Leaner Than Ever', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1478-revision-5', '', '', '2012-08-11 17:29:27', '2012-08-11 14:29:27', '', 1478, 'http://localhost/arcc/arcc/?p=1524', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1525, 1, '2012-08-11 18:57:05', '2012-08-11 15:57:05', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Epitomizing teamwork and harmony, the three major groups that compose Team Qurayyah made a ''pact'' to be united in heart and mind in achieving thier common goal to finish the project on time, with the desired quality objective, without any incients.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Composed of 570 employees from ARCC and 50 employees from contractor MHI and owner SEC, the three groups arranged themselves to from a heart-shape for the photo. For them, the heart unifies the countries - Saudi Arabia (owner), Japan (client), and Philippines.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Though coming from different countries, unity is expressed through the language of love, communicating that respect builds harmony among peoples from different cultures.</p>', 'Qurayyah Team Unity', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1494-revision-4', '', '', '2012-08-11 18:57:05', '2012-08-11 15:57:05', '', 1494, 'http://localhost/arcc/arcc/?p=1525', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
