(1654, 1, '2011-09-20 13:46:24', '2011-09-20 10:46:24', '<strong>The Earth-Breaking Ceremony of the Manifa Training Center and Plant Model for the Saudization Program</strong> was inaugurated recently with Mr. Norman K. Macapagal (SVP – KSA Operations) and Al Rushaid Petroleum Investment Company’s (ARPIC) Hossam Kh. Al Rahyyem (VP – Administration and Industries Support) with Khalid A. Al Abdul Aziz (Group Human Resources Manager). Joining them in the affair were the Executive Management from Saudi Aramco, Mohammed A. Abdul Karim (Manifa Development Program Manager) and Mohammed A. Al Mana (Senior Project Manager of Manifa Program).\r\nThe vision of using a Plant Model for the Saudi Personnel Enhancement and Skills Development Program was originally designed by the Manifa Project Manager Edwin T. Paragas. He saw the need of hands-on training so that the Saudi workers’ skill and confidence will be developed prior to the actual work at the project site. It is their objective to improve the performance of the Saudi workforce through these training facilities and by adopting Saudi Aramco standards.\r\nUpon completion of the program, the participants will be given a Saudi Aramco Certification Qualifications.', 'Manifa Training Center and Plant Model', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'manifa-training-center-and-plant-model', '', '', '2012-08-31 16:55:50', '2012-08-31 13:55:50', '', 0, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/?p=1654', 0, 'post', '', 0),
