(1697, 1, '2012-08-23 14:22:09', '2012-08-23 11:22:09', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;"><strong>EEI Corporation ’s subsidiary in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia , Al Rushaid Construction Company, LTD.</strong>, completed several key project milestones in the Saudi Aramco Manifa Utilities, Storage, and Shipping Facilities Project. As of September, 2011, the project was 52.79% accomplished, 2.65% ahead of schedule.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The Manifa Development Program, an important increment in Saudi Arabia’s Capital Program is designed to increase petroleum output in response to increasing world energy demand. This offshore field is designed to produce 900,000 barrels per day (bpd) of extra capacity to Saudi Arabia’s oil output. This will also produce 120 million scfd of sour gas, 50,000 bpd of condensate, and 950,000 bpd of produced water. The central processing utility of the Manifa Offshore Oil Field also aims to process one billion cubic feet per day of natural gas.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The significant highlight of the project is the completion of Pipe Rack Structures (with a total weight of 6197 tons). The installation of miscellaneous structures is still ongoing.<p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As far as mechanical works is concerned, 156 out of 175 sets of equipment (equivalent to 92.83% progress) have already been installed. The work progress for welded-type pipes is already at 58.80% progress, while progress for the flangetype pipes is at 42.20%.<p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The total instrument cables that have been pulled is 121,040 out of 355,900 linear meters, (lm). 82.13% or of the total cable trays have been installed while 229,482 out of 532,025 lm of the total cables have already been pulled out.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Painting Works is already 9.46% accomplished while Insulation Works is schedule to start in October.<p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">ARCC will perform 65% of the total works for the Manifa Central Processing Facilities (also known as Package 2), which includes Mechanical, Electrical, and Instrumentation Works for the Manifa Central Producing Facilities and its associated plants as well as the Crude Storage and Shipping Pumps, Water Oil Separation Plant, Water Injection Plant, Reverse Osmosis Utility, and Ponds and West Manifold Facilities.<p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The project started last September 15, 2010 and has an on-site workforce of about 1,667 with 4,122,406 recorded manhours without Lost Time Accident.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">This plant, in which Japan Gas Corporation and ARCC play major roles, is of high importance to Saudi Aramco and to Saudi Arabia as well, as it will deliver the necessary feedstock for the diversification of KSA’s downstream industries.</p>', 'Manifa Project in full swing!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1650-revision-6', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:22:09', '2012-08-23 11:22:09', '', 1650, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1697', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
