(1698, 1, '2012-08-23 14:19:43', '2012-08-23 11:19:43', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">To maintain a worklife balance, promote health awareness, and eliminate poor work habits, the Al Rushaid Construction Company Ltd. (ARCC) launched its Fitness and Wellness Program.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The program entitled, "Walk, Skip, and Jump for Health" attracted hundreds of health aficionados during its kick-off last September 16, 2011 at the ARCC Jubail Main Camp. The program started with opening remarks from Mr. Romulo B. Lazaro (Senior Administration Manager), who emphasized the importance of being healthy and fit. He encouraged all personnel to participate in the company''s initiative. "We designed this concept for an important reason and that is to make each of you active and live healthiereveryday," Lazaro said.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The members of the Executive Management lead by Mr. Mercado T. Magno (Vice President and General Manager for Operations) and Norman K. Macapagal (Senior Vice President) were fully supportive of the program. They stressed on the value of having a healthy mind, body, and spirit. "Health is wealth. I hope through the introduction of this Fitness and Wellness Campaign, we can sustain high morale of our employees, increase participation not only in number but in sincerity so they can reduce stress and lower the risk of serious health problems," Macapagal explained.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">"Let us all enjoy, go out, and have fun. Make use of this program to ease your boredom. While we are getting involved in this wonderful undertaking, your families back home need you as much as we need you here in the ARCC Saudi Arabia Operation," Magno said.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The program was declared open by Joey J. Rosal (ARCC Senior Manager for Personnel Services) and was hosted by Peter B. Lomboz.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The three-month "Walk, Skip, and Jump for Health" is a group competition exclusively for employees only. Prior to the opening, each employee gathered in the center court for callisthenics. At the end of the program, a charity Fun-Run will be organized in order to draw more participants and achieve its goals. The event will be held simultaneously in all ARCC camps and project locations.</p>', 'ARCC: Fitness & Wellness Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1659-revision-6', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:19:43', '2012-08-23 11:19:43', '', 1659, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1698', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
