(1683, 1, '2012-08-18 18:03:24', '2012-08-18 15:03:24', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The full welding of these Boiler Tubes, having "zero" clearance in-between was skillfully performed and completed as a result of continuous training at Qurayyah''s Welding Academy applying the combination of using mirror and flexible head TIG torch.</p>', 'Incredible skills and performance...', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1008-revision-10', '', '', '2012-08-18 18:03:24', '2012-08-18 15:03:24', '', 1008, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/?p=1683', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1684, 1, '2012-08-22 15:17:56', '2012-08-22 12:17:56', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Epitomizing teamwork and harmony, the three major groups that compose Team Qurayyah made a ''pact'' to be united in heart and mind in achieving thier common goal to finish the project on time, with the desired quality objective, without any incients.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Composed of 570 employees from ARCC and 50 employees from contractor MHI and owner SEC, the three groups arranged themselves to from a heart-shape for the photo. For them, the heart unifies the countries - Saudi Arabia (owner), Japan (client), and Philippines.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Though coming from different countries, unity is expressed through the language of love, communicating that respect builds harmony among peoples from different cultures.</p>', 'Qurayyah Team Unity', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1494-revision-9', '', '', '2012-08-22 15:17:56', '2012-08-22 12:17:56', '', 1494, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/?p=1684', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1685, 1, '2012-08-11 18:18:45', '2012-08-11 15:18:45', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Al Rushaid Construction Co., Ltd. (ARCC) affirms its commitment to protect and prevent injuries and ill-health of all its employees, resources, properties and interested parties against human suffering and financial loss resulting from accidents and to pursue continual improvement in OH&S management and OH&S performance.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As of the 3rd quarter of 2010, ARCC has already accomplished several milestones of Safe Manhours on its existing projects: Shuqaiq II Independent Water Power Plant project achieved 14.4 million Safe Manhours, National Chevron Philips (North Plot Project) recorded 10.5 million Safe Manhours, and Qurayyah Power Plant Boiler Modification Project registered 1.5 million Safe Manhours.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">With the attainment of OHSAS 18001:2007 certification, ARCC has taken its Health, Safety, Security and Environmental (HSSE) Management System to a higher level and has equipped itself with the following programs:</p><ul style="list-style-type:circle !important;text-align: left;"><li> HSSE Documentation System</li><li>HSSE Organization / Staff</li><li>Job Hazard and Risk Assessment</li><li>HSSE Meeting and Communication Process</li><li>Employee HSSE Orientation, Training, Awareness and Competence Program</li><li>Program Monitoring and Surveillance (HSSE Inspection & Audit)</li><li>Incident Investigation and Reporting</li><li>Emergency Response & Preparedness</li><li>HSSE Statistics</li><li>HSSE Incentive Program</li><li>Management Review and Improvement Process</li></ul><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">To be more effective, these programs are conducted in a structured management system that is integrated within ARCC, conducted by top management and with full commitment from all levels and functions in the organization.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">"Safety should not just be propaganda or a catchy poster displayed for everyone to see, it should be ingrained in the system by the individuals involved in the project and the entire organization," says Mercado T. Magno, VP and General Manager. "I congratulate everyone involed in promoting and maintaining a safe and accident-free work place. We should continue to propagate a culture where everyone is consciously working safely in thier daily routines. Safety awareness and continuous education are important tools to ensuring success of our programs." Magno adds.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">As a way of ensuring that safety is instilled in everyday life, Safety Awareness is now included in weekly coordination meetings of officers and senior staff. "Safety Moment" participants are asked to share insights on safety issued they encountered, not only within the organization but also those observed from others as well. Mercado T. Magno included this portion in the weekly meetings so that participants can learn and improve, as well as prevent unsafe practices.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">"''What can go wrong?'' is a question we should always ask ourselves" is what ARCC Corporate HSSE Manager Ramil V. Escarmosa repeatedly says during the core group meetings. Being conscious of this at all times will ensure the successful implementation and achievement of the Company''s HSSE objectives and management system programs.</p>', 'ARCC: Safety Milestone', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1484-revision-9', '', '', '2012-08-11 18:18:45', '2012-08-11 15:18:45', '', 1484, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc/?p=1685', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
