(1700, 1, '2012-08-23 14:17:11', '2012-08-23 11:17:11', '<p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The ARCC Manifa Project Management Team organized the first employees’ Fun Day entitled, “Summer Saya sa Manifa” with the theme “Coming Together is a Beginning, Keeping Together is Progress, Working Together is Success”. This activity was held at the Manifa Beach Camp last September 1, 2011. Around 1,600 project employees participated in the event.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">The event aimed to imbibe the concept of teamwork, and improve job ownership, communication, and work excellence through the group games. It was designed to acquire camaraderie, sense of belongingness,and workplace harmony for the Field Operation Group, Support Group, and Management. It is to promote a work-life balance, which is an ingredient to a healthy working environment.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Mr. Roy L. Virtucio (Project QA/QC Manager) delivered the opening remarks and thanked the Manifa Project Management Team and employees for their cooperation that made the event successful. According to him the event was an effective avenue to break the monotony of life in the camp and that it was a way of promoting social consciousness.</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;">Mr. Edwin T. Paragas (Group Manager for Operations) likewise acknowledged the participation of each employee, thanked the Executive Management for their support, and congratulated the organizing committee for a job well done. He then talked about the theme,</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;"><font style="font-style:italic">Coming Together is a Beginning</font> – “The Manifa Project is comprised of different nationalities and regions in the Philippines, but it is united through a mission – and that is to work hard for our loved ones back home and provide decent lives for our children. It is a beginning of a great time; we are all here to work with quality and safety, and to complete the project on time.”</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;"><font style="font-style:italic">Keeping Together is a Progress</font> – “Everyone should share their expertise in order to maintain high productivity with a proactive lifestyle in the Manifa Project.”</p><p style="text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;text-indent: 40px;"><font style="font-style:italic">Working Together is a Success</font> – “I encourage everyone to support and be a part of the company’s objective. We are in a critical stage of the project and we hope to continue the momentum for the successful completion of the project. The Saudi Aramco Manifa Central Processing Facilities is not only important to our company but to the Saudi Arabian economy as well.”</p>', 'Summer Saya sa Manifa!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1663-revision-6', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:17:11', '2012-08-23 11:17:11', '', 1663, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1700', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
