(1740, 1, '2012-08-27 10:17:04', '2012-08-27 07:17:04', 'Al Rushaid Construction Co. Ltd. has successfully retained its ISO 9001:2008 accreditation for another 3 years in the re-certification audit conducted last March 5-6, 2012 by T&#xDC;V NORD. Since 2006, ARCC has maintained its ISO certificaton including its transition from ISO 9000:2000 standard to ISO 9001:2008.\r\nARCC is the first construction company which has attained ISO 9001 Quality Management System accreditation on 2008 standard version, and this was specially mentioned by the T&#xDC;V Nord auditors: Dr. Arshad Ali Naqvi (Auditing Manager and Lead Auditor) and Muhamed Ameen Valliyengal (QMS Auditor) during their opening meeting.\r\nThey also said that ARCC is consistent in complying with its established Quality Management System. This consistency shows the dynamism of the organization in implementing, following, and monitoring its QMS with regard to the (ARCC) client''s requirements. Dr. Naqvi added that continual improvement process will be looked into during the re-certification audit.\r\nPresent during the opening meeting at the ARCC Head Office in Al Khobar are officers of the company, headed by Norman K. Macapagal (Senior Vice President and General Manager) and Mercado T. Magno (Vice President and General Manager for Operations). Both officers echoed Dr. Naqvi''s remarks on improvement as they talked about the organizational efficiency already being implemented in the Company, including the revisions to the policies and procedures.\r\nThe Company is proud that its services meet the highest quality levels which generate total customer satisfaction. Maintaining ISO 9001 standards is a milestone and of prime importance for the entire team of QA/QC Department.\r\n"Getting through the re-certification audit and obtaining its approval has made ARCC more confident in delivering quality services to its customers and in return gaining respect from our existing and prospective clients, which ecentually win us more projects", according to Fortunato R. Solis, Jr. (Senior AVP- Corporate QA/QC).\r\nARCC operates in the Kingdom for the construction of major industrial facilities of Aramco, Saudi Arabia Basic Industries Corporation (SABIC) and Saudi Electric Company (SCESO). Amoung its major clients include Bechtel, TECHNIP, Worley-Parsons, JGC, MHI and Samsung.\r\nThe audit process of the first day included an interview with Top Management, Marketing, Engineering, Contracts, Procurement, Central Logistics and Administraton, Equipment / Tools, the Management Representative and Central DCS. During the second day of audit, T&#xDC;V Auditors visited ARCC''s SAMCO Acrylic Acid Plant Project in Jubail Industrial City. An introductory meeting was held wih Project Manger Ronnie Domingo and all his PMT staff. The audit started with the Project Manager and Project Control, followed by QC, Purchasing, Equipment Section and Warehouse. Assisting the T&#xDC;V NORD auditors were ARCC Management Representative [MR] Manuel C. Bisbal and QMS Lead Auditor Oliver M. Estrella, both certified by the International Registry of Certificated Auditors (IRCA).\r\nDuring the closing meeting held at ARCC Central Training Room in Juaymah, Dr. Naqvi and his co-lead auditor Muhammed Ameen acknowledged the strengths of the Company. "You have a very good and effective training and development program, competent workforce, and most importantly strong management commitment on quality and these are the Company''s strong points," said Dr. Arshad Ali Naqvi.\r\nMr. Norman K. Macapagal, Senior Vice President and General Manager extends his warmest congratulations to the entire team and said, "We know the value of having strong commitment to quality standards. We will be able to earn the respect and confidence of our clients. This re-certification will continue to prove that our operations are at par with some of the international contractors operating in the Kingdom. Quality and organizational efficiency will continue to be a trademark of ARCC, thus realizing our vision in becoming the contractor of choice."', 'ARCC is ISO 9001:2008', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1446-revision-12', '', '', '2012-08-27 10:17:04', '2012-08-27 07:17:04', '', 1446, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1740', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1741, 1, '2012-08-31 16:43:33', '2012-08-31 13:43:33', 'Al Rushaid Construction Co. Ltd. has successfully retained its ISO 9001:2008 accreditation for another 3 years in the re-certification audit conducted last March 5-6, 2012 by T&#xDC;V NORD. Since 2006, ARCC has maintained its ISO certificaton including its transition from ISO 9000:2000 standard to ISO 9001:2008.\r\nARCC is the first construction company which has attained ISO 9001 Quality Management System accreditation on 2008 standard version, and this was specially mentioned by the T&#xDC;V Nord auditors: Dr. Arshad Ali Naqvi (Auditing Manager and Lead Auditor) and Muhamed Ameen Valliyengal (QMS Auditor) during their opening meeting.\r\nThey also said that ARCC is consistent in complying with its established Quality Management System. This consistency shows the dynamism of the organization in implementing, following, and monitoring its QMS with regard to the (ARCC) client''s requirements. Dr. Naqvi added that continual improvement process will be looked into during the re-certification audit.\r\nPresent during the opening meeting at the ARCC Head Office in Al Khobar are officers of the company, headed by Norman K. Macapagal (Senior Vice President and General Manager) and Mercado T. Magno (Vice President and General Manager for Operations). Both officers echoed Dr. Naqvi''s remarks on improvement as they talked about the organizational efficiency already being implemented in the Company, including the revisions to the policies and procedures.\r\nThe Company is proud that its services meet the highest quality levels which generate total customer satisfaction. Maintaining ISO 9001 standards is a milestone and of prime importance for the entire team of QA/QC Department.\r\n"Getting through the re-certification audit and obtaining its approval has made ARCC more confident in delivering quality services to its customers and in return gaining respect from our existing and prospective clients, which eventually win us more projects", according to Fortunato R. Solis, Jr. (Senior AVP- Corporate QA/QC).\r\nARCC operates in the Kingdom for the construction of major industrial facilities of Aramco, Saudi Arabia Basic Industries Corporation (SABIC) and Saudi Electric Company (SCESO). Amoung its major clients include Bechtel, TECHNIP, Worley-Parsons, JGC, MHI and Samsung.\r\nThe audit process of the first day included an interview with Top Management, Marketing, Engineering, Contracts, Procurement, Central Logistics and Administraton, Equipment / Tools, the Management Representative and Central DCS. During the second day of audit, T&#xDC;V Auditors visited ARCC''s SAMCO Acrylic Acid Plant Project in Jubail Industrial City. An introductory meeting was held wih Project Manger Ronnie Domingo and all his PMT staff. The audit started with the Project Manager and Project Control, followed by QC, Purchasing, Equipment Section and Warehouse. Assisting the T&#xDC;V NORD auditors were ARCC Management Representative [MR] Manuel C. Bisbal and QMS Lead Auditor Oliver M. Estrella, both certified by the International Registry of Certificated Auditors (IRCA).\r\nDuring the closing meeting held at ARCC Central Training Room in Juaymah, Dr. Naqvi and his co-lead auditor Muhammed Ameen acknowledged the strengths of the Company. "You have a very good and effective training and development program, competent workforce, and most importantly strong management commitment on quality and these are the Company''s strong points," said Dr. Arshad Ali Naqvi.\r\nMr. Norman K. Macapagal, Senior Vice President and General Manager extends his warmest congratulations to the entire team and said, "We know the value of having strong commitment to quality standards. We will be able to earn the respect and confidence of our clients. This re-certification will continue to prove that our operations are at par with some of the international contractors operating in the Kingdom. Quality and organizational efficiency will continue to be a trademark of ARCC, thus realizing our vision in becoming the contractor of choice."', 'ARCC is ISO 9001:2008', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1446-revision-13', '', '', '2012-08-31 16:43:33', '2012-08-31 13:43:33', '', 1446, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1741', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1742, 1, '2012-08-31 16:51:54', '2012-08-31 13:51:54', '<strong>The Earth-Breaking Ceremony of the Manifa Training Center and Plant Model for the Saudization Program</strong> was inaugurated recently with Mr. Norman K. Macapagal (SVP – KSA Operations) and Al Rushaid Petroleum Investment Company’s (ARPIC) Hossam Kh. Al Rahyyem (VP – Administration and Industries Support) with Khalid A. Al Abdul Aziz (Group Human Resources Manager). Joining them in the affair were the Executive Management from Saudi Aramco, Mohammed A. Abdul Karim (Manifa Development Program Manager) and Mohammed A. Al Mana (Senior Project Manager of Manifa Program).\nThe vision of using a Plant Model for the Saudi Personnel Enhancement and Skills Development Program was originally designed by the Manifa Project Manager Edwin T. Paragas. He saw the need of hands-on training so that the Saudi workers’ skill and confidence will be developed prior to the actual work at the project site. It is their objective to improve the performance of the Saudi workforce through these training facilities and by adopting Saudi Aramco standards.\nUpon completion of the program, the participants will be given a Saudi Aramco Certification Qualifications.', 'Manifa Training Center and Plant Model', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1654-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-31 16:51:54', '2012-08-31 13:51:54', '', 1654, 'http://192.168.8.59/arcc-eei/?p=1742', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
